He is currently a welterweight fighter in the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]], where, as of the end of 2006, he has compiled a record of 4-2 in UFC competition. During his sixth fight for the UFC, a victory against [[Tony DeSouza]], Alves tested positive for a [[diuretic]], [[Spironolactone]], which he admitted he used to cut weight to the 170 lb. welterweight limit.<ref>{{cite news 
|first= Josh
|last= Gross
|authorlink= 
|coauthors= 
|title= NSAC Says Alves Tests Positive for Diuretic
|url= http://www.sherdog.com/news/news.asp?n_id=6483
|work= Sherdog.com
|publisher= 
|date= [[2007-01-04]]
|accessdate=2007-01-29 }}</ref>

He is currently associated and trains with [[American Top Team]].

